1 NAME Hilma Eleanor /Kokkinen Clusiau/
2 GIVN Hilma Eleanor
2 SURN Kokkinen Clusiau
2 NICK Eleanor
1 SEX F
1 BIRT
2 DATE 23 Nov 1916
2 PLAC Nashwauk, Minnesota
1 DEAT
2 DATE 21 May 2008
2 PLAC Ely, Minnesota
2 SOUR @S5@
3 DATA
4 DATE Friday, May 23, 2008
4 TEXT Eleanor Clusiau, 91, of Ely passed away peacefully on May 21.
5 CONT
5 CONT She was born in Nashwauk to Finnish immigrant parents John and Mina Kokkinen. She married Arlie Clusiau and together they owned Clusiau Motor Sales in Ely from 1947-1958, the Babbitt Bowling Center in Babbitt and Clusiau Lincoln-Mercury in Roche
5 CONC ster where she worked side-by-side with her husband as the office manager. She continued to summer in Ely at her Burntside Lake cabin after her husband died in 1969 and moved to Ely permanently in 1983.
5 CONT
5 CONT She personified "sisu" and enjoyed fishing, golfing and bowling and was an avid cribbage player right up to the end, counting her own cards and sometimes correcting her cribbage partners' counts. Always a perfectionist, she took great pride an
5 CONC d satisfaction in maintaining her house and yard. In her later years, she was very interested in politics, enjoyed Newsweek, and watching all the TV political talk shows, being especially careful to monitor what the "other side" was saying. Sh
5 CONC e knew her values and had strong opinions on just about anything that was going on. She never, ever failed to vote, often looking forward to "voting the rascals out."
5 CONT
5 CONT She is survived by her daughters, Marilyn Johnson (Bruce) of White Bear Lake and Shirley Kapsch (Steve) of Lake Oswego, OR, six grandchildren and 12 great grand children. She was the last of the Kokkinen family of Nashwauk, three brothers Eero
5 CONC , Ernest and Edmund Kokkinen and two sisters Ayla Merila and Sylvia Sarell.
5 CONT
5 CONT Private services will be held with burial in Hibbing. The family suggests memorial contributions to the Ely-Bloomenson Community Hospital Foundation, 328 West Conan St., Ely, MN 55731.
5 CONT
