1 TITL Consanguinity Chart
1 ABBR Consanguinity Chart
1 REPO @REPO1@
1 TEXT For a true "relationship" to exist, there must be an ancestor who is common to both individuals.
2 CONT
2 CONT Let us suppose that you have a grandson of that common ancestor and you want to know that grandson's relationship to a great-granddaughter. Go across to the second generation (Grandson or daughter) and then down to the third generation (Great Gr
2 CONC andson or Daughter), the resulting relationship is 'First Cousin Once Removed.'
2 CONT
2 CONT http://www.mngs.org/tools.shtml
